<html>   
<head>   
<title>H.R. 1039</title>   
</head>   
<body>   
<center><font size=6><b><a name="top">H.R. 1039</a></b></font></center>   
<p>   
  <PRE>
104th CONGRESS 
1st Session 
To amend the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 to repeal the estate and 
gift taxes and the tax on generation-skipping transfers. 
                   IN THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES 
                          February 24, 1995 
Mr. CRANE (for himself, Mr. BLUTE, Mr. MCKEON, and Mr. HANCOCK) 
    introduced the following bill; which was referred to the 
    Committee on Ways and Means 
                               A BILL 
To amend the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 to repeal the estate and 
gift taxes and the tax on generation-skipping transfers. 
 [Italic->]   Be it enacted by the Senate and House of 
Representatives of the United States of America in Congress 
assembled,  [<-Italic] That (a) chapter 11 of the Internal Revenue 
Code of 1986 (relating to estate tax) is hereby repealed. 
  (b) Chapter 12 of such Code (relating to gift tax) is hereby 
repealed. 
  (c) Chapter 13 of such Code (relating to tax on 
generation-skipping transfers) is hereby repealed. 
  (d)(1) The repeal made by subsection (a) shall apply to the 
estates of decedents dying after the date of the enactment of this 
Act. 
  (2) The repeals made by subsections (b) and (c) shall apply with 
respect to transfers made after the date of the enactment of this 
Act.

</PRE>  
<p>    
