<HEAD>

<TITLE>Background Paper -- TRC</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Microsoft Word 2.0z Beta">
</HEAD>

<BODY>
<center>
<P><h2>TRC Background Paper</h2>
<P>
by <a href="/taxcom/bios.html#Kemp">Jack Kemp</a>
</center><P>

<blockquote>
<hr>

<P>
The National Commission on Economic Growth and Tax
Reform is holding a series of public hearings to investigate problems
with the current income tax system and principles of tax reform.
<P>
Senate Leader Bob Dole and House Speaker Newt Gingrich
have charged our 14-member commission with making recommendations
for a tax code that is &quot;flatter, fairer, and simpler&quot;
-- a system that will encourage economic growth and greater opportunity
for all Americans.
<P>
Senator Dole and Speaker Gingrich asked commissioners
to study ways in which the current tax code -- with its &quot;high
marginal tax rates and thousands of pages of rules, regulations,
and red tape -- poses a barrier to economic growth.&quot; As they
said:
<UL>
<LI>It punishes the most dynamic forces for growth
in our economy -- the small business owners and entrepreneurs
who turn bold ideas into new businesses, new jobs, and new products.
</UL>

<P>

<UL>
<LI>It discourages working Americans who are trying
to save for the future and to build a better life for themselves
and their families.
</UL>

<P>

<UL>
<LI>It is endlessly complex and confusing, costing
literally billions of dollars in lost time and effort.
</UL>

<P>

<P>
One of the most important aspects of our work is
to talk with Americans from all walks of life -- small business
people, farmers, factory workers, inventors, and entrepreneurs
-- who make America work. We will be holding hearings across the
country over the next several months to talk with taxpayers and
to hear from experts who study tax policy.
<P>
We believe that tax reform must move toward making
the tax code more family friendly and create incentives for savings
and investment.  We want to help guide the debate toward changes
that will reinvigorate entrepreneurship, risk taking, savings,
investment, and work effort.  And we hope to contribute to changes
that will make America more competitive and expand the nation's
worldwide leadership in the 21st century economy. 
<P>
We know far too much about what doesn't work, and
we know that those who are hurt the most by bad public policies,
especially tax policy, are those at the bottom of the economic
ladder. 
<P>
While there is overwhelming anger and frustration
with the current system, we need to explore more about citizens'
experiences with problems and solutions before we can go forward
with radical change.
<P>
For example, what are the implications to the economy
of a steeply progressive tax system? What is the impact on economic
growth of higher marginal tax rates? What do people mean whey
they say they want a &quot;fairer&quot; tax system?  What do we
mean by &quot;flatter&quot; tax rates?  There are a lot of different
views, and we want to know what the American people think and
what are the ramifications.
<P>
I am proud to serve with the distinguished men and
women on this commission who have offered to give of their time
and energy and talents so that all Americans can have a better
chance at the American dream. Individually and collectively, my
colleagues on the commission have a huge font of knowledge, experience,
and courage that can help guide our work.
<P>
We are setting the stage for a 21st century tax policy
for America.  It is imperative that everyone work together to
advance this monumental task.  
<P>
What we are undertaking may feel at times like moving
a mountain. Making the tax code simpler will be a very complicated
process.
<P>
We hope that this series of hearings -- in which
both citizens and experts present views -- will help all of us
to learn more and to make better informed decisions about the
hard choices that lie ahead. If we can find the core, central
principles of a new vision for tax reform that includes everyone's
views, we can get this done. The American people -- and our children
and grandchildren-- will be the winners.
</blockquote><P>
<P>
<center>
[ <a href="/taxcom/">TRC Home</a> ]
</center>

</BODY>

