		<b>CHAIRMAN KEMP:</b>  Any other?  <p>

		Gary.<p>

		<b>MR. MULLER:</b>  I'd like to address the issue of
big versus small.<p>

		A friend of mine just returned from Georgia,
the country of Georgia.  And there they are starting to
divide their country up into private enterprise.  And
one of the things that they're trying to set up is
create farm land that the individual owns.  <p>

		But what they're trying to set up is about two
hectare plots per person.  That's about five acres.<p>

		What five acres is going to do for those people
is going to guarantee that they are going to be
peasants the rest of their life.<p>

		And as I stated in my testimony, we're not out
here just trying to survive and create a subsistence
life.  <p>

		We don't need to be looked at as second class
citizens as a group of farmers.  We're going to be out
