<html>
<head>
<title>TRC - News Release</title>
</head>
<body>
<h3><center>COMMISSION GOAL - A FLATTER, FAIRER AND SIMPLER TAX SYSTEM</h3></center>

<p>
<p>
	<b>WASHINGTON, D.C., JUNE 14 --</b> "Designing a flatter, fairer and simpler tax system 
that will encourage economic growth and greater opportunity for all our people," is how Jack 
Kemp described his goal as Chairman of the recently formed National Commission on 
Economic Growth and Tax Reform.
<p>
"Senator Dole and Speaker Gingrich had it exactly right," Kemp said, "when they 
announced the formation of the National Tax Reform Commission and said that the current 
federal tax code with its high marginal rates and thousands of pages of rules, regulations and 
red tape, poses a formidable barrier to economic growth.  It is quite frankly a disaster for 
everybody.  It is a system that needs not just reform but a complete overhaul.  We must 
concentrate on creating a tax code for the 21st century."
<p>
In his charge to the members of the National Tax Reform Commission Kemp said, "Tax 
reform must move toward making the tax code family friendly and create incentives for work, 
savings and entrepreneurship.  The congressional leadership has asked the National 
Commission on Economic Growth and Tax Reform to start with a blank piece of paper and 
design a system that is flatter, fairer and simpler -- one that will encourage strong economic 
growth and greater opportunity for all."
<p>
"The Commission will gather the views of American citizens from all walks of life and 
collect and analyze the best available analysis and evidence from the experts who study tax 
policy.  The Commission is expected to issue its recommendations and its report in December.  
The Commission’s report will provide recommendations that will contribute to reinvigorating 
entrepreneurship, risk-taking, savings, investment, and work efforts.  Our goal is to produce a 
report that will make America more competitive, expand the nation’s worldwide leadership in 
the 21st century global economy, and help eliminate, where they exist, any conditions of 
despair and poverty," Kemp said.
<p>
Commission members include Loretta H. Adams, President, Market Development, Inc.; 
J. Kenneth Blackwell, Ohio State Treasurer; Herman Cain, Chairman and CEO, Godfather’s 
Pizza, Inc.; Carroll A. Campbell, Jr., former Governor of South Carolina; Pete du Pont, former 
Governor of Delaware; Jack Faris, President and CEO, National Federation of Independent 
Business; Edwin J. Feulner, President, The Heritage Foundation; Matt Fong, California State 
Treasurer; Ted Forstmann, Partner, Forstmann Little & Co.; Dean R. Kleckner, President, 
American Farm Bureau Federation; Shirley D. Peterson, former IRS Commissioner; John 
Snow, Chairman, President and CEO, CSX Corporation; and John Wieland, President, John Wieland Homes, Inc.
<p>
<center>[ <a href="/taxcom/">TRC Home</a> ]</center>
</body>
