<a name="north">
<H3>North to Deliver Keynote Address at Richmond Conference on November 15-16</H3>
Foundation regional conferences have established a nationwide reputation for being the most effective training grounds for America's conservative student leaders. 
 Thousands of students have participated in these informative weekend conferences, and have been spurred on to greater activism as a result.  
<table align=left width="200" hspace="5">
<tr><td><IMG SRC="ollie.gif" ALT="Ollie North" WIDTH=250 HEIGHT=272>
<BR><B>Oliver North </B>will deliver Friday night's banquet 
address at the Richmond Conference.</I></td>
</tr>
</table>
<P>The next Foundation regional conference will be 
held on <B>November 15-16 </B>at the Omni Hotel in Richmond, 
Virginia.  <B>Oliver North </B>will be the keynote speaker on Friday 
evening, November 15, and <B>M. Stanton Evans</B>, author of 
<I>The Theme is Freedom</I>, will be among those 
addressing the conference on Saturday, November 16.  (Additional speakers will be confirmed as the date draws nearer.)
<P>If you are a full-time college student, this 
conference is <B>FREE</B> of charge, but advance 
registration is mandatory.
<P>
<BR>The two-day conference is the perfect way to sharpen your 
campus activism skills in order to become a more effective advocate 
of your beliefs.  Whether you are an experienced activist or are 
just becoming involved, we welcome your participation.  So, tell your friends and conservative 
club members to put Nov. 15-16 on their calendars today.
<P>The Richmond conference will allow you to bring some balance 
to your one-sided liberal education by exposing you to the 
principles of free market economics, the virtues of traditional American 
values, and the brilliance of our Founding Fathers.  Attending 
this conference is the best way to motivate yourself to change your 
campus.  As Oliver North said, &quot;We weren't put here to simply 
endure the future... we are here to change it for the good.&quot;
<P>To register for the Richmond Conference, call 
<B>Kristen Kingsley</B> today at 1-800-292-9231.
<P>
