<a name="program"><center><h3>
Foundation Lecture Program to Feature Justice Clarence Thomas, Vice-President Dan Quayle, William F. Buckley, and Jack Kemp<br></h3></center></a>
This spring, Young America's Foundation is sponsoring one of its most exciting line-up of speakers to-date.  Spring lecturers include Vice-President <B>Dan Quayle</B>, 75th Attorney General <B>Edwin Meese</B>, and the Christian Coalition's <B>Ralph Reed</B>.  
<P>In the month of April, the Foundation will be sponsoring Associate Supreme Court Justice <B>Clarence Thomas </B>at Southeast Missouri State University, former Congressman and HUD Secretary <B>Jack Kemp </B>at Loyola University-Chicago, and <I>National Review </I>Founder <B>William F. Buckley 
</B>at Weber State University.
<P>If you are interested in sponsoring a Foundation speaker at your school, call 
<B>Michelle Sharp </B>at 1-800-292-9231.
