<TITLE>Press Releases</TITLE>

<body bgcolor="#ffffff">

<center>
<a href="/townhall/FRC/images/topban.map">
<img src="/townhall/FRC/images/topban.gif" ismap border="0"></a>
<img src="/townhall/FRC/press/pressban.gif"></center>
<br>

The Family Research Council works daily with the media to ensure that the 
<B>Pro-Family Voice</B> is heard.
<P>
The Family Research Council is active in taking its message to the gatekeepers 
of the public airways and print publications, presenting critical information 
necessary for a balanced approach to the story of the American family. Often, 
FRC is the only pro-family voice heard by opinion shapers controlling radio, 
television and print.  Daily, the national media - from CNN on television to 
print leaders like the <i>Wall Street Journal</i> - contact FRC's network of 
experts.
<p>
Our most recent news releases are shown below. To receive other FRC news 
releases and/or monthly policy mailings, contact the FRC media office at 
<b>(202) 393-2100.</b>
<p>
Otherwise, you can receive our press releases via email using our online 
<a href="/townhall/FRC/subscribe/subscribe.html.cgi">subscription form</a>. 
This way you will never miss a press release!

