<html>

<title>Gary L. Bauer, President</title>

<body bgcolor="#ffffff">

<center>
<img src="/townhall/FRC/whois/whois.gif">
</center>

<p>

<center>

<h2><font size=+3>G</font>ary <font size=+3>L.</font> 
<font size=+3>B</font>auer</h2>

<h3>President</h3>

<p><hr size=3 width=65%><p>
<img src="/townhall/FRC/photos/frc11.gif">
<p><hr size=3 width=65%><p>

</center>

<P>
An audio welcome message from Gary L.
Bauer:<BR><UL><UL>
<A HREF = "/townhall/FRC/audio/message.wav">(WAV format 217K)</A><BR>
<A HREF = "/townhall/FRC/audio/message.au">(AU format 158K)</A>
</UL></UL><P>

As president of the Family Research Council, Gary Bauer directs the course of the pro-family policy and lobbying group in its nationwide efforts to address family issues.  A nationally known speaker and commentator, Mr. Bauer is active in the political process in the nation's capital and at the grassroots level.  
<P>
Mr. Bauer joined the Council in October 1988, when the Washington, D.C. based organization merged with Focus on the Family.  Mr. Bauer was also Senior Vice President of Focus on the Family until Family Research Council became a separate organization on October 1, 1992. 
In 1991, Mr. Bauer was Chairman of the successful Citizens Committee to Confirm Clarence Thomas.
<P>
Prior to joining FRC, Mr. Bauer served as Assistant to President Reagan for Policy
Development and Director of the Office of Policy Development in the White House.  He held this position the last two years of the Reagan Administration.
<P>
Before Mr. Bauer's presidential appointment in January of 1987, he was appointed Under Secretary of the U.S. Department of Education beginning in July 1985, when he was confirmed by unanimous vote by the U.S. Senate.  Mr. Bauer first joined the department in 1982 as Deputy Under Secretary for Planning, Budget & Evaluation.  He was also the department's representative on the White House Cabinet Council for Human Resources and was Chairman of the Working Group on School Discipline that delivered its report to the President in 1984.  
<P>
In June 1986, Mr. Bauer was named Chairman of President Reagan's Special Working Group on the Family.  His report, "The Family:  Preserving America's Future," was presented to the President in December, 1986.  Mr. Bauer also served in the Reagan-Bush campaign as a Senior Policy Analyst and worked in the Office of the President-Elect as Assistant Director for Policy/Community Services Administration.
<P>
<P>
Mr. Bauer is the author of <A HREF="/townhall/FRC/whois/bauerdoc.html#journey"><I> Our Journey Home
</I></a>published by Word, Inc. in October 1992, and is co-author of
<A HREF="/townhall/FRC/whois/bauerdoc.html#children"><I> Children at Risk: The Battle for the Hearts and Minds of Our Kids </I></A>written with Focus President and Founder, Dr. James Dobson.  
<P>
In 1968, Mr. Bauer received his B. A. degree from Georgetown College in Georgetown, Kentucky, and Juris Doctorate from Georgetown Law School in Washington, D. C. in 1973. 
<P>
<B> AREAS OF EXPERTISE:</B>
<UL>
	<LI> Pro-family politics and strategies:  from the grass roots to the White House
	<LI> The social issues agenda
	<LI> Family issues and partisan politics
	<LI> The devaluation of values
	<LI> Religious freedom
	<LI> Foundations for strong families and communities
	<LI> Implementing pro-family legislation
	<LI>  Family time famine
	<LI>  Family tax relief
	<LI>  Education and the conservative Reagan dynasty
</UL>

<p><HR SIZE = 3 WIDTH = 60%><p>

<center>
<a href="/townhall/FRC/images/navstrip.map">
<img src="/townhall/FRC/images/navstrip.gif" ismap border="0"></a>
<br>

