<title>Kenneth R. Weinstein - Heritage</title>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/heritage/paperh.jpg">			





<h3>KENNETH R. WEINSTEIN</h3>
<hr>
<b>DIRECTOR, GOVERNMENT REFORM PROJECT</b>
<P><IMG SRC="/heritage/staff/pics/weinstei.gif" ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=10>
<P>

	As director of the Government Reform Project at The Heritage Foundation, a leading public policy organization based in Washington, D.C., Weinstein's research focuses on such topics as term limits, campaign finance reform, and ending taxpayer-funded lobbying.  He also coordinates Heritage's Union Watch Working Group, which examines the political activities of labor unions.  
<p>	Prior to joining Heritage, Weinstein served as director of Research at the New Citizenship Project, a Washington, D.C.-based public policy group dedicated to limiting government.  From 1991 to 1994, he served as a Research Fellow at the Hudson Institute, a conservative think tank based in Indianapolis, Indiana. 
<p>	Weinstein writes regularly on public policy issues and his articles and book reviews have appeared in numerous publications, including <I>Human Events</I>, the <I>New Republic</I>, the <I>Wall Street Journal</I>, the <I>Washington Times</I> and the <I>Weekly Standard</I>.  
<p>	A New York City native, Weinstein earned his bachelor's degree in General Studies in the Humanities from the College of the University of Chicago. He holds a master's degree in philosophy from the Institute for Political Studies in Paris and a Ph.D. in political science from Harvard University.  
