<html>
<title> John S. Barry - Heritage</title>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/heritage/paperh.jpg">


<h3>John S. Barry</h3>
<hr>
<b>Policy Analyst</b>
<P><IMG SRC="/heritage/staff/pics/barry.gif" ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=10>
<P>
John S. Barry is an Economic Policy Analyst within the Thomas A. Roe Institute for Economic Policy Studies at The Heritage Foundation, a Washington, D.C. based public policy institute.  Mr. Barry concentrates on general economic issues, including federal taxation and banking/financial sector regulation.

<p>
Mr. Barry received a Bachelor of Arts degree with honors in Economics and Government from the University of Notre Dame.  While at Notre Dame, he was the editor-in-chief of a campus magazine for three years.  Mr. Barry is currently pursuing his Ph.D. in Economics at George Mason University.
<p>
Before joining the staff of The Heritage Foundation, Mr. Barry operated a small residential painting business in his home state of Ohio.
<p>
Mr. Barry has been active in the budget, tax, and regulation debates since joining the staff of The Heritage Foundation.  He is the Foundation's lead analyst on banking and financial service sector regulation issues. He has contributed to numerous Heritage Foundation studies including the 1995 book, <i>Rolling Back Government, A Budget Plan to Reinvent America</i>. He also has authored and co-authored several papers and newspaper articles featured in various publications including <i>The Washington Times</i>, <i>The Journal of Commerce</i>, and <i>Investor's Business Daily</i>. 



